ArticleCleaner.java
Provides utilities for reading, cleaning, and processing article text.
Returns an array separating each word with a space, devoid of
non alphanumeric characters.
Methods:
assignArticle(); //Recieves article and splits it
readFileasString(); //File Reader Method
fileToArrayList(); //Takes file and converts the split string into
array
//Also removes all non- alphanumeric characters
WordFrequency.java
Creates two arrays in order to calculate the frequency of words.
Takes in clean array of data from ArticleCleaner and counts the
frequency of words.
WordCount class is helper class.
countWordFrequencies(); //Creates two arrays and loops so that if
a unique word is foud, it adds 1 to the counter
StopWordSort.java
Has its own reader to read the articles, compare the words inside
of the article to the list of stop words, and remove those words.
Prints the output as a string.
removeStopWords(); // Takes in the file for stopwords, and compares
each stopword with the individual token in the
tokenized article. It then returns a new
arraylist with all the stop words removed.
WordCount.java
Takes information from cleaned article class, and prints the word
counts for each article.
CountWordsUsingSplit(); //takes input, splits, and then counts the
length of the array.
CountWordsInArrayList(); //Takes array of words and creates a
string of all the words, returns the
combined string
Attitude.java
Takes files of positive and negative words, and searches the article
for them. Then it tallies and compares to see if article is positive
or negative.
countPositiveSentiment(); //Takes input of arraylist of tokenized
words in the article and compares it to
the list of words in positive-txt and tallies.
countNegativeSentiment(); //Takes input of arraylist of tokenized
words in the article and compares it to
the list of words in negative-txt and tallies
analyzeSentiment(); //Takes the ints of the counted postive and
negative words, and returns whether the article
is positive or negative.
RichWordCount.java
Simply counts up the amount of unique words in an article. If it tries
to count a word it has already counted, it will skip and move to the
next word
countUniqueWordFrequency(); // takes in arraylist of a tokenized article
loops through each index of the article and increases word count. Then
returns the amount of unique words in the article.
repeatedWords.java
Sorts through each word of the articles and adds a new count for each
unique word. After that, it prints the amount of occurrences of each
word.
countUniqueWordFrequency(); // takes in arraylist of a tokenized article
loops through each index of the article and increases word count. Then
returns the amount of unique words in the article.
